N2  - This article looks at issues surrounding student participation on a school's board of trustees. The author discusses some of the issues that have confronted university presidents, and caused some to become more public relations oriented personas rather than decision makers. The author asks if student, faculty, or administration participation on the boards of trustees might be more effective. The article considers the impact of student participation in decision making, as they are the consumers of higher education.
