DO  - 10.5465/amj.1969.19209697
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 9
EP  - 10
VL  - 12
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article comments on issues within the academy, such as the future, the role, change, quality, operationality, relevance, openness, and vitality. The author argues that the academy must be relevant, operational and address itself to outward as well as inward concerns. Organizations such as the Academy of Management must accommodate change, must remain forward- and outward-looking, and challenging in order to remain relevant. The author suggests that in order for the Academy of Management to maintain its credibility as a professional and academic society, it must address interdisciplinary studies, upgrade scientific components, continue to demand laboratory and field substantiation of research, and exercise rigor in the developing the organization.
AB  - This article comments on issues within the academy, such as the future, the role, change, quality, operationality, relevance, openness, and vitality. The author argues that the academy must be relevant, operational and address itself to outward as well as inward concerns. Organizations such as the Academy of Management must accommodate change, must remain forward- and outward-looking, and challenging in order to remain relevant. The author suggests that in order for the Academy of Management to maintain its credibility as a professional and academic society, it must address interdisciplinary studies, upgrade scientific components, continue to demand laboratory and field substantiation of research, and exercise rigor in the developing the organization.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amj.1969.19209697
